JOHANNESBURG - Mpumalanga Premier Refilwe Mtshweni-Tsipane has confirmed that two people have been arrested in connection with the assault and robbery of Dr Esther Mahlangu. Mtshweni-Tsipane said one suspect was found in possession of Mahlangu's gun. The 87-year-old world renowned Ndebele artist was attacked in her Siyabuswa home last month. She was robbed of an undisclosed amount of money and a firearm. Mtshweni-Tsipane made the announcement a short while ago while visiting Mahlangu's home. "They will appear in court tomorrow [Friday] . We have briefed the family and briefed the chieftaincy around here," she said.